## Dev fixtures — contents ignored by default (e.g. the large data-warehouse
## fixture isn't tracked), with the bundled demo project allow-listed because
## it's shipped in the .app and the build phase reads from it. The pattern has
## to be `fixtures/*` rather than `fixtures/` so the negation below works —
## git can't un-ignore a file under a fully-ignored directory.
fixtures/*
!fixtures/demo-coffee-shop/
